==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Arminian
<hw>Ar*min"i*an</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to Arminius of his followers, or to their doctrines. See note
under <er>Arminian</er>, <pos>n.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arminian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Arminian
<hw>Ar*min"i*an</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eccl. Hist.)</fld> <def>One
who holds the tenets of Arminius, a Dutch divine (b. 1560, d.
1609).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>The Arminian doctrines are: 1. Conditional election and
reprobation, in opposition to absolute predestination. 2. Universal
redemption, or that the atonement was made by Christ for all mankind,
though none but believers can be partakers of the benefit. 3. That man,
in order to exercise true faith, must be regenerated and renewed by the
operation of the Holy Spirit, which is the gift of God. 4. That man may
resist divine grace. 5. That man may relapse from a state of
grace.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arminianism</ent>⟦br⟧
